 {\rm E}[X]=\sum_{k=0}^\infty P(X>k). 
\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}\mathbb P(X=k)=\mathbb P(X>0).
\sum_{k=2}^{\infty}\mathbb P(X=k)=\mathbb P(X>1).
\sum_{k=3}^{\infty}\mathbb P(X=k)=\mathbb P(X>2)
\mathbb E[X]=\sum_{k=0}^{\infty}\mathbb P(X>k)
\begin{matrix} P(X>0) &= &P(X=1) &+ &P(X=2) &+ &P(X=3) &+ &P(X=4) &+ &\cdots\\ P(X>1) &= & & & P(X=2) &+& P(X=3) &+  &P(X=4) &+ &\cdots\\ P(X>2) &= & & &  && P(X=3) &+  &P(X=4) &+ &\cdots\\ P(X>3) &= & & &  & &  &  &P(X=4) &+ &\cdots\\ \vdots &\vdots \end{matrix}
\displaystyle \sum_{k=0}^\infty P(X>k) = P(X=1)+2P(X=2)+3P(X=3) + 4P(X=4)+\cdots
